      "span_text": "The left panel of figure 14 shows τ (z) B 0 ,n B for B 0 = 3 nG, while the right panel shows the visibility function defined by g(z) ≡ dτ dz e −τ (z) . Strikingly, even a few nG field yields the optical depth to z ∼ 10 3 of order unity, which is clearly ruled out by the fact that we can still see the CMB temperature power spectrum at l 100. Therefore, the optical depth provides an additional constraint on the field strength [CITATION_1] ."
